&lt;li&gt;&lt;input disabled="" type="checkbox"&gt; Third-party library pitfalls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today we talked about a vulnerability in a recently released third-party logging library that can be exploited with minimal effort to execute remote commands. A logging library and remote command execution seem completely unrelated, yet over-engineered third-party libraries are everywhere.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The more code I read, the more I feel that a lot of open-source code is of very poor quality—regardless of how many k-stars it has. Stars represent needs, not engineering skill.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Design Specification Template</title><link>https://blog.jqknono.com/en-us/blog/2024/06/28/design-specification-template/</link><pubDate>Fri, 28 Jun 2024 17:35:07 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.jqknono.com/en-us/blog/2024/06/28/design-specification-template/</guid><description>&lt;ul&gt;
